text.section:
A dissolved limited cooperative association may notify its known claimants of the dissolution in a record. The notice shall:
Provide the name of the association;
Specify that a claim be in a record;
Specify the information required to be included in the claim;
Provide an address to which the claim must be sent;
State the deadline for receipt of the claim, which may not be less than one hundred twenty (120) days after the date the notice is received by the claimant; and
State that the claim will be barred if not received by the deadline.
